{
  "stem": "10825.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But we were ruined.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had to start from the beginning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this-- this is Poland for you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we went on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We lived.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And until the war-- it was before-- it was in 1938 it was already.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When Hitler came to-- to Germany, when he took over Germany, it started anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Poles, the [INAUDIBLE] they were called, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] took over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they did everything that they could to-- to-- to spoil for Jews their living.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And later in '39, before it broke out the war, they didn't let into-- to Jewish stores, they picketed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and then it was-- it was a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we-- we couldn't imagine what awaits us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we knew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew what's going on in Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There-- there was-- it wasn't like-- like television.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or, radio was a little bit already, but-- but the newspapers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were well read.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were well informed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What was going on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we knew what we have to await.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "For instance, our professionals, they couldn't study in-- in Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They have got to go abroad, like doctors, journalists.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Or-- but we had very, very intelligent and able people, Jews, who worked.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "For instance, we had a wonderful poet by the name of Julian Tuwim, who was a Polish poet.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But if he would have remained in-- in Poland, he would have ended in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Luckily, he went out of Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when he came back-- and while he was creative, he-- he didn't felt himself like a Jew.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's like the Jews in Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were Jews of-- of Moses' belief.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You understand?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "First they were Germans.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then there were-- and there they were-- they were Jews of Moses' beliefs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it was assimilation like-- like-- like we have it here.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
